description:
Responsibilities

Assist superior in Company’s full range financial accounting functions, particularly revenue accounting functions and account receivable functions, treasury and cash management functions including billing, rebate scheme implementation, credit and cash management control and debt collection.
Assist superior to supervise a small team of cashier to carry out cash collection functions at Cargo Terminal.
Assist in liaising with auditors, bankers, airlines, tax representation, Inland Revenue Department and Hong Kong Airport Authority etc.
Liaise with holding company to ensure information and schedules were provided timely and accurately.
Supervise the revenue accounting team to perform month-end closing process including monthly commitments and monitor timely interfaces between finance system and other systems etc.
Prepare ad hoc reports / analysis whenever required

 Requirement

Degree holder in Accounting / Finance or related discipline with professional qualifications i.e. ACCA, HKICPA or equivalent;
Minimum 5 years' accounting experience in terminal, warehouse, logistics or freight forwarding industry of which minimum 2 years at supervisory level;
Capable to manage small team and work independently;
Experience in SAP or similar accounting system is preferred;
Proficient in Microsoft Office applications;
Mature, independent, responsible and able to meet tight deadline;
Team player with strong organisation and communication skills;
Good command of both written and spoken English and Cantonese.
To apply, you may email your confidential resume with date of availability, current and expected salary to recruitment @cpsl.com.hk. Applicants not contacted within 6 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful.
Cathay Pacific Services Limited is an Equal Opportunities Employer. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with our personal data policy and for recruitment purposes only. Candidates not notified within six weeks may consider their application unsuccessful. All related information will be kept in our file for up to 24 months.

Key Responsibilities:


Support the development and operation of talent development programmes by working with both internal departments and external partners including training service providers, NGOs and higher education institutions;
Plan, coordinate and organise events and training workshops for education & the talent development programmes;
Take part in different events, projects or initiatives to facilitate community companies in recruiting and engaging talents;
Drive business collaboration to catalyze the expansion of partner companies; and
Perform any other duties as assigned by supervisors or management.

Requirements:



University graduate in Business, Science, Engineering or related discipline.
Minimum 6 years of relevant work experience in education / learning programme development and operation, preferably in STEM related discipline at tertiary education level;
Experience in handling funding programmes, academic institutions and NGOs;
Good understanding of working with college / university students is preferred;
Proactive team player with excellent problem-solving skills, pleasant and outgoing with excellent communication and interpersonal management skills across the Corporation and with outside partners as well as enthusiastic about working with students;
Proactive team player with excellent problem-solving skills, pleasant and outgoing with excellent communication and interpersonal management skills across the Corporation and with outside partners as well as enthusiastic about working with students;
Proficiency in both spoken and written English and Chinese (including Putonghua)
The position is on a renewable 2-year fixed-term contract, subject to performance and operational needs, the position will convert into open contract after 2 years.


We offer competitive package to the right candidate. Interested party please click Apply Now to apply on or before 11 February 2022 in confidence with full resume in Word document, stating present and expected salary, and available date and quote the reference. 

Applicants who do not hear from us by 25 February 2022 may assume that their applications are unsuccessful.

Further information about the Cyberport is available at http://www.cyberport.hk

Responsibilities

Responsible for executing strategic plans to achieve sales targets and expand the customer base in eCommerce channel specialize in overseas marketplace;
To develop and execute full spectrum of marketing and sales plans including budget, brand management, product pricing and trade marketing programs;
Work close with different teams to monitor and improve operations including but not limited to order management, fulfillment, order forecast, inventory management, preparing business analysis reports;
Manage product mix and assortment planning on assigned platforms;
Analyze business trends and consumer insights and evaluate existing product categories on choices;
Suggest appropriate go-to-market strategies and plans;
Work closely with 3rd party platforms, agencies & in-house designers for marketing service support and ad hoc projects;
Lead a team to ensure smooth operation in various channels and drive sales to support a fast growing businesses.
Requirements

University graduate with at least 5 years’ experience in eCommerce/ retail management preferred;
Knowledge across SEM, Social Media and Affiliates;
Experienced in cross-border marketplaces and eCommerce operations is absolutely advantage;
Good in numerical sense;
Hard-working with positive attitude;
Able to work under pressure and meet the deadlines;
Detail-oriented, with a high level of accuracy and ability to process and analyze data;
Fast learner and willing to face challenges;
Strong communication in written and spoken English, Cantonese, with Putonghua is an advantage;
Proficiency in MS Office including MS Excel.


We offer

5 - day work week
Medical Benefits
Annual Merit Bonus
Staff Purchase Discounts
Staff Recreation Activity
Shuttle Bus Service
Education Sponsorship

Interested parties please send a full resume with current and expected salary by email by clicking APPLY NOW:

Please visit our corporate website at http://corp.sasa.com/en/home to know more about us.

(Sa Sa is an Equal Opportunity Employer and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment. Personal data collected will be kept confidential and used for recruitment purpose only.)

Job Responsibilities

1. Develop quantitative trading strategy and perform risk analysis

2.Collect trading data and perform historical analysis

3.Construct arbitrage model parameters and perform adjustment based on long-term market profits

4.Work closely with developers to propose/execute improvements

5.Strong interest in quantitative trading and motivation of discovering new strategies

Requirements

1.Strong academic background, statistics or quantitative finance major preferred;

2. At least 3 years’ experience or above solid related experience gained in sizeable organisation or listed companies is preferred;

3. Knowledge of trading strategy in Equities, Futures & Commodities;

4. Result oriented, highly self-motivated, with the ability to work independently and under pressure;

5. Strong analytical skill and numerical sense;

6. Basic knowledge in crypto products and trading is a plus

Responsibilities:

1. Conduct market research on market trend, industry index, impact from the policy update, etc.

2. Conduct research and analysis of industries/companies independently and provide analysis reports

3. Strong interest in equity investments and motivation of discovering investment opportunities

Requirements:

1. Bachelor Degree holder or above in Business Administration, Finance, Medical, Computer Science or related disciplines;

2. Minimum 2 years of relevant working experience gained in Dot-com or blockchain industry;

3. Excellent interpersonal skills and be able to work under pressure with minimal supervision;

4. Excellent command of written and spoken English and Chinese

Responsibilities:

 Assist Directors to prepare business proposals

Business Scope including product, preject, oversea project and service.

Closely liaise with investors and Top Management

Handle ad hoc assignments when needed.

Requirements:

 Degree or above in Finance, Hospitality, Business Administration, Real Estate , Legal, Trading or relevant disciplines;

At least 3 years working experience in similar capacity;

Proactive, energetic and be able to work in a fast-paced environment;

Good presentation and interpersonal skills;

Good command in both spoken and written Chinese and English;

Interested parties, please Click Apply to application.

Candidates not notified within one month should consider their applications unsuccessful.

Personal data collected is for recruitment purpose only and will be treated in strict confidence. Unsuccessful applications will be destroyed within 3 months from the date of application.

Responsibilities:

Manage e-commerce operations including order processing, product checking, inventory control and logistics with relevant departments;
Assist in customer enquiries, order tracking, online payment and refund issues;
Identify new sales opportunities via EDM, cold/warm calls, plan and budget for appropriate online marketing strategies;
Coordinate with night shift buyer to plan and execute the product listing on eshop;
Liaising and coordinating with related departments to ensure smooth daily business operations;
Handling ad-hoc operations tasks on E-Commerce platform

Requirement:

Bachelor Degree in business or related discipline;
Strong sense of responsibility, enthusiastic approach and excellent presentation and interpersonal skills;
Good communication skills in written and spoken English and Chinese;
Proficiency in PC applications, such as MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Chinese word processing;
Working location: Yau Ma Tei
Working hours: 10am-7pm
Bank Holiday, 8 days rest day each month

Responsibilities


Support to Business Development team including the preparation of sales order and quotation, delivery arrangement not limited to samples, sales reports, data entry and photo shooting of products;
Work closely with principals and suppliers for the product information, customer enquiries and complaints;
Assist in comprehensive filing and record system for sales agreement and commercial correspondence;
Work closely with internal teams to ensure the product launch in chain stores and e- commerce platforms;
Assist in ad hoc projects as required;

Requirements

Diploma/ High diploma  holder in Business Administration, Marketing or related disciplines;
At least 2-years of relevant sales support experience;
Excellent customer services and communication skills;
Independent, hardworking and willing to work under pressure;
Good time management skills and well organized;
Proactive and positive learning attitude;
Proficient in both written and spoken English and Chinese, Putonghua is an advantage;
Proficient in MS Excel, PowerPoint & Chinese Word Processing;
Immediate available is preferred

We offer competitive salary and good opportunity to the right candidate.

(All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only and will be treated in accordance with our Personal Data Policy, which is available immediately upon request. Our Company reserves the right to modify the terms and conditions of package offered.)
